From 1b8fd79c25b4ca991883e20c8a2f71aa93d53fe7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: t <t@t.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 21:14:47 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix RF 'reads once then stops': end search session via
 waitForCardAbsent()
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Root cause (confirmed from AAR bytecode of RFCardReaderDeviceImpl):
- The RF reader is a PROCESS SINGLETON over the native JNI layer
  (RFCardInterface, static rfcardinterfaceLock). getDevice() always
  returns the same object, so 'open a fresh handle per read' was an
  illusion — same singleton, same stale native search state.
- waitForCardPresent() does clear() -> searchBegin() -> wait -> getCard()
  and NEVER calls searchEnd() on success. The ONLY correct way to end
  that native search is the device's own waitForCardAbsent(), which runs
  the MEMBER searchEnd() that balances searchBegin().
- Earlier attempts failed because: close()/reopen tore down native state;
  and calling the raw static RFCardInterface.searchEnd() corrupted the
  singleton's bookkeeping (that's why nothing scanned at all).

New pattern:
- ensureRfDevice(): open the singleton ONCE, cache it, skipRATS.
- readNfcOnce(): waitForCardPresent -> read UID/type -> endSearchSession()
  (= device.waitForCardAbsent(800ms)) so the NEXT poll can searchBegin.
  Also called on timeout/no_card so an aborted search is always balanced.
- recycleRfDevice(): full close+clear only on hard error / detach.
- All RF ops serialized under rfLock on the io thread (no ANR).

flutter analyze clean; APK 37.7MB (arm64).
---
 .../ValidatorHardwarePlugin.kt                | 209 +++++++++++-------
 1 file changed, 134 insertions(+), 75 deletions(-)

diff --git a/android/app/src/main/kotlin/com/transurban/transurban_validator/ValidatorHardwarePlugin.kt b/android/app/src/main/kotlin/com/transurban/transurban_validator/ValidatorHardwarePlugin.kt
